result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Karina G Ronzon in court with attorney Gabriela A Leija.  Dax Odom appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties are prepared to enter into a deferred prosecution agreement.
AS TO COUNT 1
Court GRANTED state's motion for Count 1 to be Dismissed, but Read In.

Defendant Karina G Ronzon in court with attorney Gabriela A. Leija.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties have reached a resolution through a DPA.  Defense counsel requests case be set DPA Hearing. All conditions of bail remain in effect. Case adjourned to branch 23.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for April 28, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
$100.00 bail to be returned. Oral No Weapons Order  Pre-trial conference scheduled for 03-19-2015 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Benjamin R. or his residence or place of employment

Defendant Karina G Ronzon in court.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.   Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant.
Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance.  Defendant IS Public Defender eligible.  Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  The case is adjourned to Br.23  for a Pretrial Conference.vb
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 3/5/15 @ 1:30pm
